tion for M-giant stars extends to M_bol = -6.0 mag, and that for C stars\nspans -5.6 < M_bol < -3.0. The bolometric luminosity function of C stars is\nunlikely to be a Gaussian distribution and the mean bolometric magnitude of C\nstars is estimated to be M_bol = -4.24 \\pm 0.55, which is consistent with our\nresults for dwarf elliptical galaxies NGC 147 and NGC 185.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 May 2012 07:11:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
